user_question: What are the key differences between beach volleyball and indoor volleyball?
final_answer: Key differences include the number of players (2 per team in beach volleyball vs. 6 in indoor), the playing surface (sand vs. hard court), the size of the court (beach courts are smaller), and the scoring system (rally scoring to 21 in beach vs. 25 in indoor).
